Mon Jun 06 18:47:40 2005  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/packhand.c:

	Backport: fix a menu update problem: when a unit is selected the
	"load"/"unload" menu choices are sensitized or desensitized
	correctly, but later the (un)loading of another unit can cause
	this sensitivity to become wrong. The fix is just to update the
	menus when a nearby unit is (un)loaded.

	Reported by Christian Knoke <chrisk@cknoke.de> in PR#12679.

