Thu Mar 31 17:48:36 2005  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* server/connecthand.c, server/stdinhand.c:

	Backport: don't aitoggle a player until all info is sent to the
	client. This bug occurrs in /take or when connecting directly to
	a player in a running game; doing the aitoggle first triggers a
	player packet which the client cannot correctly handle, and
	because of delta no second packet may be sent.

	Reported by Marko Lindqvist in PR#11612. Patch by Mike Kaufman
	and myself.

Thu Mar 31 17:37:58 2005  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

