Fri Oct 01 17:53:02 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* server/unithand.c:

	branches: 1.308.2; Change map_pos_to_tile and native_pos_to_tile
	to do wrapping. index_to_tile returns NULL for invalid indices.
	Users are changed so that separate calls to normalize_map_pos and
	map_pos_to_tile are not needed. Users of native_pos_to_tile
	become much simpler because there was previously no way to wrap
	in native positions.

	Patch by me in PR#10393.

Fri Oct 01 17:53:02 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* server/generator/mapgen.c:

	branches: 1.12.2; Change map_pos_to_tile and native_pos_to_tile
	to do wrapping. index_to_tile returns NULL for invalid indices.
	Users are changed so that separate calls to normalize_map_pos and
	map_pos_to_tile are not needed. Users of native_pos_to_tile
	become much simpler because there was previously no way to wrap
	in native positions.

	Patch by me in PR#10393.

Fri Oct 01 17:53:02 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* common/map.c:

	branches: 1.199.2; Change map_pos_to_tile and native_pos_to_tile
	to do wrapping. index_to_tile returns NULL for invalid indices.
	Users are changed so that separate calls to normalize_map_pos and
	map_pos_to_tile are not needed. Users of native_pos_to_tile
	become much simpler because there was previously no way to wrap
	in native positions.

	Patch by me in PR#10393.

