Thu Sep 30 15:13:58 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* common/aicore/path_finding.c:

	branches: 1.24.2; Don't try to step in the direction referenced
	by an unitialized variable. Instead we initialize the direction
	to -1, and don't do any step from the source tile of a
	constructed patch.

	Patch by me in PR#10392.

Thu Sep 30 15:09:17 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* server/settlers.c:

	Avoid a crash in consider_settler_action when a log call accessed
	a tile pointer that was unitialized. The fix is to initialize it
	to NULL so that the logging happens properly.

	Reported by Egor Vyscrebentsov <evyscr@murom.net> in PR#10386.

