Thu Sep 09 17:23:41 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* common/connection.h:

	Use specvec to make a byte_vector to hold the network code's
	compression queue. This makes for simpler code and will quite a
	bit more efficient on systems that use a naive realloc
	implementation.

	Patch by me in PR#9947.

Thu Sep 09 17:23:41 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* common/connection.c:

	branches: 1.43.2; Use specvec to make a byte_vector to hold the
	network code's compression queue. This makes for simpler code and
	will quite a bit more efficient on systems that use a naive
	realloc implementation.

	Patch by me in PR#9947.

Thu Sep 09 17:23:41 2004  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* common/packets.c:

	Use specvec to make a byte_vector to hold the network code's
	compression queue. This makes for simpler code and will quite a
	bit more efficient on systems that use a naive realloc
	implementation.

	Patch by me in PR#9947.

