	Patch by me in PR#9909.

Sat Sep 04 07:46:03 2004  Mateusz Stefek <mstefek@poczta.fm>:

	* ai/advdiplomacy.c:

	Currently it's (almost)impossible to agree on cease fire with AI
	player, even if you aren't his war target. This is really wrong.
	This patch changes the behavior of AI love, so that it gravitates
	towards -28, not -100 when you are at war, but aren't his target.

	Now you can have cease-fire with computer for 3 cities and 3
	advances :)

Sat Sep 04 07:41:40 2004  Mateusz Stefek <mstefek@poczta.fm>:

	* ai/advdiplomacy.c:

	Allow AI to break 3-man pact. It should be considered as bug in
	PR#9884. Patch by me.

