	good reason.

Tue Sep 23 18:53:08 2003  Gregory Berkolaiko <Gregory.Berkolaiko@math.tamu.edu>:

	* server/sanitycheck.c:

	Kill the hugely annoying assert(!pplayer->is_dying). Jason
	promises to fix it some time.

	Patch by Jason, after complaints by me.

Tue Sep 23 18:43:23 2003  Gregory Berkolaiko <Gregory.Berkolaiko@math.tamu.edu>:

	* ai/advmilitary.c:

	Remove dead (unfunctional) code that tries to estimate time for
	the enemies to get to our city by boat. It was looking at wrong
	boats. Now we will only look at boats the enemies have already
	boarded.

	Patch by Per. Part of 6227.

Tue Sep 23 16:18:05 2003  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/mapview_common.c:

	Make overview coordinates be a scaling of native coordinates.
	This allows the overview to work well with iso-maps.

	Issued as PR#6178.

