Fri Jul 25 14:48:32 2003  Gregory Berkolaiko <Gregory.Berkolaiko@math.tamu.edu>:

	* client/packhand.c, client/tilespec.c, common/city.h,
	common/unit.c:

	This patch cleans the usage of pcity->occupied up in two ways:

	1. Instead of pcity->occupied it's now pcity->client.occupied.
	This makes it harder to accidentally use it at the server (which
	was one of the original bugs with this code), and is a prelude
	for more client-side-only fields (see PR#3771). Of course this
	means all users have to be changed.

	2. Lots of comments added about the client-side usage of this
	field. It seems that the client side of the code is correct, so
	some explanations are put into the comments.

	Patch by Jason.

