Sun Jan 12 18:04:08 2003  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/packhand.c, common/nation.c, common/nation.h,
	data/nation/american.ruleset, server/ruleset.c:

	Remove the hard-coded limit on the number of leaders that a
	nation can have. Allocate space for the leaders on-demand, so as
	not to take up large quantities of unused memory. There is still
	a limit of MAX_NUM_ITEMS (currently 200) leaders imposed by the
	network code.

	Patch by Raimar Falke <rf13@inf.tu-dresden.de> as PR#2598 with
	changes by me.

