Thu Nov 07 19:31:39 2002  Egbert Hinzen <egbert@hinzen-koeln.de>:

	* po/de.po:

	updated

Thu Nov 07 19:21:12 2002  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/gui-xaw/graphics.c:

	In gui-xaw, when cropping a sprite, if the sprite has no mask
	then don't try to crop one. This prevents warnings from cropping
	a NULL mask (which happens when using PNG graphics files).

Thu Nov 07 18:55:26 2002  Raimar Falke <i-freeciv-forward@rf.risimo.net>:

	* common/nation.c, common/player.c, server/handchat.c,
	server/handchat.h, server/maphand.c, server/plrhand.c,
	server/ruleset.c, server/savegame.c, server/srv_main.c,
	server/stdinhand.c:

	Add teams. A team is a group of players that start out allied,
	with shared vision and embassies, and fight together to achieve
	team victory with averaged individual scores. Team are controlled
	via the new server command "team". Teams can't change after the
	game has started.

	Patch from Per I. Mathisen <per@leftist.net>.

Thu Nov 07 18:55:25 2002  Raimar Falke <i-freeciv-forward@rf.risimo.net>:

	* server/gamelog.h:

	branches: 1.9.2; Add teams. A team is a group of players that
	start out allied, with shared vision and embassies, and fight
	together to achieve team victory with averaged individual scores.
	Team are controlled via the new server command "team". Teams
	can't change after the game has started.

	Patch from Per I. Mathisen <per@leftist.net>.

