Wed Nov 06 19:50:59 2002  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/gui-gtk-2.0/graphics.c:

	In gui-gtk and gui-gtk-2.0, when cropping a sprite, if the sprite
	has no mask then don't try to crop one. This prevents warnings
	from cropping a NULL mask (which happens when using PNG graphics
	files). Also, drop ctor_sprite() in favor of ctor_sprite_mask() -
	the latter takes the place of the former if the mask is NULL.

Wed Nov 06 10:23:58 2002  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/gui-gtk-2.0/gui_main.c:

	In put_conv(), make sure to allocate space for the trailing \0;
	otherwise there is a guaranteed segfault.

Tue Nov 05 21:00:45 2002  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* client/gui-gtk-2.0/graphics.c:

	Provide PNG support for the GTK and GTK-2.0 clients. They will
	now load a PNG sprite file in preference to an XPM one.

