Wed Oct 02 17:00:03 2002  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>:

	* common/capstr.c, common/dataio.c:

	Allow bitstrings of up to 64k length to be sent over the network.
	Add better error handling in the (inconceivable) case where this
	limit is exceeded. Add a manditory capability since this breaks
	network compatability.

	This was PR#2115.

